node.text:
How do I do it all?? Truth be told…I don’t😂

✨That being said, I do have tips and tools to stay on top of what I have going on. 

✨Today on the Basics of Bossing Up, I’m going to tell you all about why a notebook (yes, that’s right, a pen and paper in 2021) helps me get it done!

✨Watch the full episode to learn how a trusty notebook can help you focus, create, and - very important - not forget.

Comment below a tool or hack that helps you be productive!📒

node.title: Basics of Bossing Up Ep. 62: Notebooks

node.text:
My 3 step Glow Routine has entered the chat… @lovesquad @renskincare 

I say all the time that consistently sticking to routine is integral to success. My skincare routine is no different.

Clean, effective and packaged into recycled + recyclable packaging – this is my go to kit for my everyday GLOW!

Plus you get a cute @lovesquad headband and @renskincare reusable bag in addition to the full AM + PM routine.

Will you be trying it? Tell me below ✨

node.text:
🔥Oh snap, what do I do when I don’t know what to do?🔥

Here’s the deal: most of us find ourselves asking these kinds of questions often. Today, I’m giving you the answers!
⚡️Review - create some self awareness, observe your natural behavior and how it makes you feel. 
⚡️Read - lean into your resources and diversify content consumption. 
⚡️Reiterate - share what you’re experiencing and learning with your squad! 

What is a time when you didn’t know what to do, and what moves did you make to get through it?

node.title: Basics of Bossing Up Ep 61: What do you do when you don’t know what to do?

node.text:
Today on #bbu we’re talking 🔥DMs🔥
Be honest- we’ve all slid into the dms at some point, but have you ever slipped into the dms? Maybe you have. 

Let’s talk about what that’s a problem. Luckily for you, I’m going to give you all the low down on how to slide into them for support, instead of slippinginto them in an non-constructive  manner. 

Comment below a supportive comment you want to see in your DMs 😉

node.title: Basics of Bossing Up Ep. 60: DMs

node.text:
✨Instead of asking why me, ask why not me ✨

As women, we’re multidimensional people – we’re hard workers, friends, change-makers, mothers. I’m not just a one title person and I love owning that.

I’m honored to be the first woman featured in the new @adidaswomen series, Taking 5 With. Spent five minutes with the team talking about everything from my virtues to astrology to @lovesquad to @onepeloton. 🧡

I’ve put the link in bio if you want to read more. 🤩

Thanks @fourthhousecreative @lovesquad for making clothes that make us all feel connected, and look good 🤩

node.text:
THE PROCESS OF DECISION MAKING ⌛️ Today I’m talking about the second P of decision making: PROCESS. In order to make a decision we FEEL GOOD about, we have to have a structure for how we work through all the perspective we have been given, we have to have DISCIPLINE 🔑 

Call to action: think about the process that works for you 🧐 and comment below with your perspective👇🏾

node.text:
How do I do it all?? Truth be told…I don’t😂

✨That being said, I do have tips and tools to stay on top of what I have going on. 

✨Today on the Basics of Bossing Up, I’m going to tell you all about why a notebook (yes, that’s right, a pen and paper in 2021) helps me get it done!

✨Watch the full episode to learn how a trusty notebook can help you focus, create, and - very important - not forget.

Comment below a tool or hack that helps you be productive!📒

node.text:
✨Momma Knows Best✨

She used to make me sit at the table until I finished my oatmeal…oh what a time, Mrs.Love, what a time 🧐
 
Now I am OBSESSED (no joke) with a whole new kind of oatmeal.  @mush oats are gluten-free, dairy free and served cold 🥶 #mushpartner 

Not to mention,  I learned the company is owned by some cool women! Women supporting women, Momma would be proud!

I don’t just eat mush for breakfast (and yes I finish them without direction these days🤪) but pre/post workout 🏋️‍♀️ and sometimes even for dessert…don’t knock it til you try it.

 What did your parents make you eat as a kid that you love now?!?😍

node.text:
#ESPYS we did that!

✨Amazing events like this don’t happen by themselves, so let’s give some credit where credit is due! 

Shout outs and a big THANK YOU to:

✨ @carolinaherrera 👗 and @jimmychoo 👠 for dressing me, I felt 🔥 from head to toe! 

✨ doing the MOST, my glam squad, @hairxsherma 💇🏾‍♀️, @beautybyaja 💄& nails @nailsbymei 💅🏾

✨From running lines to holding my hand down slippery stairs 😂 my assistant @danyawass does a bit of it all 🤟🏾

✨Braving the rain and capturing  this LOOK 📸 Melissa Rawlins / ESPN images @melissakr13 

✨Behind the scenes, the amazing teams from @espn and @abcnework, especially those who were with us every step of the way - Colin, Josh, Benny, Erin, & @anthonymackie (you were incredible, I learned so much watching you) you ALL made this experience such a pleasure, and so much FUN! 

✨Feeling HELLA BLESSED  to do what I do with the team that supports  me 🧡

#lovesquad

node.text:
🌻Plant mamas UNITE 🌻

Talk about finding the great things in life that bring me joy. Yes, having a green thumb does take work {and lots of research hahaha} and taking strolls in the local garden for inspiration but it's all so worth it. [#ad]

How cute are @RXBAR's newest plant-based protein bars, RXBAR Plant? They are the newest addition to my plant baby collection! Plants on the outside and on the inside, can’t beat that amount of personal growth! 🌳

Planting good habits is good for you! Some good habits you can start today?

🌸Visit your local nursery for some new stems and tips about working that green 👍🏽
🌹Head to RXBAR.com to stock your kitchen with some plant-based protein bars! (link in bio)
💐Comment below how many plants you have in your home! (Bonus points if you share their names)
